<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1451,520,691]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">
A very distinctive species with large glaucous foliaceous striate stipules and dilated paraphyllidia. Endemic to the rocky slopes and rupestral habitats of the Serranías Chiquitanas where it is locally abundant at Chochis and Santiago de Chiquitos. The 
<typeStatus box="[340,388,629,655]" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">type</typeStatus>
is from Santiago de Chiquitos, where it has been collected frequently in recent years, as well as further west on Cerro Pelón, near Chochis (
<emphasis box="[624,831,664,690]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">J.R.I. Wood 16473</emphasis>
, 
<collectionCode box="[845,899,665,691]" country="Bolivia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15532" name="Herbario Nacional de Bolivia, Universidad Mayor de San Andr�s" pageId="11" pageNumber="212">LPB</collectionCode>
, K).
</paragraph>
